config MTK_QOS_LEGACY
	tristate "MTK QOS for MT6761, MT6765, MT6768"
	help
	This kernel config can be used to enable MTK QOS MT6768.
	When enabling this option, BW Limiter and BW Bound Detector
	will be enabled and set EMI hardware.
	If unsure, say N.

config MTK_QOS_BOUND_LEGACY
	bool "Enable QoS Bound Feature for Legacy MTK Chips"
	help
	  Enable this option to activate the QoS Bound feature on
	  legacy MTK chips.
	  This feature is essential for managing bandwidth and
	  ensuring the Quality of Service on these older platforms by
	  enforcing bandwidth limitations and detecting bandwidth bounds.
	  It is recommended to enable this option if you are working with
	  legacy chips to utilize the full capabilities of the QoS system.
	  If unsure, say N.